### Steps to Reproduce
Xamarin.Android > 8.3
1. Change building resources from aapt to aapt2 
2. Build solution
### Expected Behavior
Resources.Designer.cs members of class should have quite similar values 
### Actual Behavior
Values are changes. For example every member what have value 0 now have much diffrent value ex:
button_min_width = 0 change to button_min_width = 23232323.

This cause that layout elements currently are wrong displayed, mvvmcross binding didn' t work and so one.
### Version Information
This was reproduced on both Visual Studion on Windows and Visual studio for Mac.
Current Version Xamarin.Android 9.2.3
I think this is connected with changed of generator of Resource.Designer.cs
in Xamarin.Android.Common.targets:

```
<_UseManagedResourceGenerator Condition=" '$(_AndroidUseAapt2)' == 'True' ">True</_UseManagedResourceGenerator>
<_UseManagedResourceGenerator Condition=" '$(_UseManagedResourceGenerator)' == '' ">False</_UseManagedResourceGenerator>
```
And in  GenerateResourceDesigner.cs:

```
        // Parse out the resources from the R.java file
        CodeTypeDeclaration resources;
        if (UseManagedResourceGenerator) {
            var parser = new ManagedResourceParser () { Log = Log, JavaPlatformDirectory = javaPlatformDirectory, };
            resources = parser.Parse (ResourceDirectory, AdditionalResourceDirectories?.Select (x => x.ItemSpec), IsApplication, resource_fixup);
        } else {
            var parser = new JavaResourceParser () { Log = Log };
            resources = parser.Parse (JavaResgenInputFile, IsApplication, resource_fixup);

```

